snippet.textDisplay:
I was very surprised at the end of the year when I found a place in a wedding magazine that was very similar to a dream place walking through Christmas lights. I felt something unforgettable and cut out the building in the photo and stuck it in the room.
But what was more surprising was the home of the late Princess Diana, the Earl of Spencer in England. Very similar to the photo I cut out.
Last year, somehow, Lion King anime music came to my mind many times. I didn't understand the meaning.
At last, the mystery was solved by finding an article by a British prince who proposed the late Princess Diana's ring in Africa.
I think the late Princess Diana and Count Spencer are very worried about the two young princes in England. They wanted to tell it, and it might have been a mysterious coincidence. Is it related to royal secession or EU secession?
年末にクリスマスイルミネーションの中を歩いている夢の場所にとても似ている場所を結婚式場雑誌の中で見つけた時はとてもびっくりした。何か忘れられない気がしてその写真の建物を切り抜いて部屋に貼っていた。
でも、もっとびっくりしたのがそれがイギリスのスペンサー伯爵家、故ダイアナ妃の実家だった。私が切り抜いた写真ととても似ている。
私は去年、なぜかライオンキングのアニメの音楽が頭に何度も浮かんできた。意味がわからなかった。
故ダイアナ妃の指輪をアフリカでイギリスの王子がプロポーズで持って行った記事を見つけて、やっと謎が解けた。
故ダイアナの妃とスペンサー伯爵がイギリスの若い皇子二人をとても心配しているのだと思う。それを彼らは伝えて欲しくて、謎の偶然が続いていたのかもしれない。王室離脱やＥＵ離脱とも関係するのかな？
The two young British princes want to find the letter behind Harold's picture at the Spencer's Earl House. Maybe something related to Harold II. Maybe to make time for them to talk.
Then Spencer and Westminster Abbey.
In 1997, I might have been called. For some people.
George Peabody, the name I care about at Westminster Abbey.
Diana's words? "It is my greatest pleasure to reach out to the weak in the world."
And I want you to watch the Queen a little before going to Canada. There may be some changes. The two younger brothers and the younger brother may now have the only chance to talk.
Again, talk about the family. It is better to do family distortions while you are alive.
Because it is an unexplainable story, I think that it is a joke and ask someone to send a message to the young princes.
2人の若いイギリスの王子はスペンサー伯爵家でハロルドと書かれた絵の裏の文字を見つけて欲しい。ハロルド二世と関係ある何かかもしれない。二人が話す時間を作るためかもしれない。
それから、スペンサー伯爵とウェストミンスター寺院。
１９９７年、私は呼ばれていたかもしれない。ある人達のために。
私がウェストミンスター寺院で気になる名前、George Peabody．
ダイアナの言葉？「世界の弱者に手を差し伸べるのが、私の最上の喜び」
それから、少しカナダに行く前に女王様を見守っていて欲しい。何か変化があるかもしれない。古い二人の兄弟の王子と若い兄弟二人の王子、色んなことを話すチャンスは今しかないかもしれない。
もう一度、家族の話しを。家族の歪みは生きている間にした方がいい。
説明できない話しだから、冗談だと思って誰か聞いて若い王子様達に伝言して欲しい。
ｈ／ｗｈｙ＝ｙｈｗｈ＝３６０°ｅｄｄｉｅｅ５５ｈ／ｗｈｙ＝

snippet.textDisplay:
Racism Helped Drive Prince Harry and Meghan Markle Out of the UK and Away From the Royal Family, The attractive royal couple created billions in economic activity. Now they're going away. By Minda ZetlinCo-author, The Geek Gap @MindaZetlin

“Prince Harry and Meghan "stepping back" from being senior royals has financial consequences. Some Britons (and especially the same tabloids that have been attacking Markle all along) have expressed outrage that the couple say they will perform fewer royal duties, which usually include such things as ribbon cuttings and visiting schools and hospitals, given that British taxpayers have been paying for their security and funded the multi-million-pound renovation of their home. But the hugely popular couple, social influencers with millions of followers, have been revenue generators too. By one estimate, the royal wedding (which the royal family paid for) brought about a billion pounds to the British economy. This included things like foreign tourists coming for the wedding and sales of wedding memorabilia. Since then, interest in the couple has remained high, translating into sales of products bearing their images and a boon for the retail and travel industries.”

 “A statistic is often shared on social media that “five billionaires own 80% of the UK media”. Who are these five people? Supposedly:

Rupert Murdoch (owner of News International)
Richard Desmond (who was the owner of the Express and wrote porn magazines just guessing but he’s probably the protector of Prince Andrew)
Viscount Rothermere (owner of the Mail)...
and the two Barclay Brothers (owners of the Telegraph)


These billionaires are indeed, key players, and there is no doubt that the ownership of the mainstream media in the UK is concentrated in very few hands.”

snippet.textDisplay:
Oh dear. Meghan can’t do what she wants to do, be who she wants to be, & say what she wants to say? She knew exactly what being a royal meant where all of that was concerned, & there lies the true issue. She stomped her feet when she couldn’t go wherever she pleased, say what she wanted to say, & lived the life she wanted under the scrutiny of the paps. That’s all it really came down to. Everything came to a head when she went to that tennis match to watch her ‘friend’ Selena play, & she had her precious guards tell members of the public & the paps to ‘back off’ because SHE didn’t feel like being photographed that day. She had a temper tantrum over being scrutinised regarding the amount she spent over renovating the house, after her & Harry went on some long spiel about climate change / global warming / cutting back. 🤦🏼‍♀️

I get it with Harry. I actually do. What is he? 16th?! Or something absurd, in line to be king. Never going to happen. He’s never truly dealt with the passing of his Mum, I think that’s all coming to a head now because he’s now a father himself & because he’s had such intense scrutiny by the paparazzi. However, if he was still single - or dare I say, married someone else who was more accepting of the royal lifestyle - I have no doubt in my mind he wouldn’t be wanting to move half way across the world ‘to live a normal life’. Britain & his family is all he’s ever known, he’ll soon get homesick.
Meghan got her way though, now she can gallivant all over without worrying about what the paps will pick up on, because they’ll just threaten legal action. She’s definitely the type who would fight to keep Harry away from Archie if they split, but Harry has more power behind him than she’ll ever know.

I am happy he’s trying, & I hope he does get help for what I feel is PTSD regarding his mothers sudden passing. I just hope he hasn’t closed too many doors..’just in case’.
